text:
hello friends, colleagues and community!

we have been seeing the #metoo movement transform people's understanding of rape culture in phenomenal ways. despite the many cons of call-out culture and survivors of sexual violence being further traumatized, we are seeing sexual violence being discussed in the public like never before.
we are also seeing more binary thinking and polarization of survivors versus perpetrators in this discussion. however, what about people who have survived sexual violence and also perpetrated? what happens when they want to access therapy services to change?
for the last 5 years, i have been working with this dual identity of people, in different capacities in india and in the us. to address the systemic violence and to end rape culture, i, as an art therapist find it crucial to not distance ourselves as health-care providers from people who have been harmed and have caused harm. 
how do we do this?

i've been presenting a public art showcase on:
- working with people who identify as both - survivors and perpetrators of sexual violence in one body.
- being a therapist who works with this population and how it impacts my view of sexual violence
- asking you- how do we hold accountability beyond #metoo within clinical and community mental health spaces? how do we address the need for services here?

today was the second of a series to come. my heart is full with gratitude towards all those who showed up to be a part of the dialogue. i wish i could get pictures with everyone!- but your presence, your thoughts and your contribution to this discussion was so essential. thank you. thank you for all your help in making this happen in numerous ways!

#arttherapistwork
#community #accountability #artwork #artbasedresearch #patricialeavy
#sonyashah #jung #vanderkolk #trauma #sexualviolence #traumatherapy #poetry #artsbasedresearch

text:
по совету @elchichek_22 я посмотрела мультик “фердинанд”. как и обещали - умывалась слезами от умиления. а еще, для меня этот мультик является самой яркой илюстрацией того, что такое настоящая сила. 
к большому сожалению, многие люди воспринимают доброту и искренность за слабость, а агрессию - за силу. 
когда-то я даже спорила с преподом о том, что мужчина, который плачет на глазах у женщины - он демонстрирует силу, или слабость？ я считаю, что силу （если не делает это через день, конечно 😊）. потому что показать свои слабые места - это смело. 
сказать: “мне здесь больно. сюда не лезь, пожалуйста” - это сильно, потому что человек будет знать, что вам здесь больно, и сможет использовать это как для вас, так и против вас. это требует от человека в первую очередь признать в себе свои больные места, и не нападать на окружающих по поводу и без. а это ой какая работа над собой. 
агрессоры часто могут казаться сильными, но это не так. вы видели когда-то, чтобы они искренне говорили о своих чувствах, не манипулируя？ вы видидели, чтобы они говорили о том, что для них тяжело, при этом не требуя ничего？  это звучит парадоксально, но жертва с агрессором - одинаково слабы. потому что любой агрессор - всегда в прошлом жертва. просто агрессор в какой-то момент решил не быть, а казаться сильным и могучим. но это не так. наверное, я это пишу, чтобы самой окончательно выйти из этой роли. 
однажды, я, находясь в абьюзивных отношениях （токсичных, другими словами） - сказала “мы расстаемся”, и просто перестала играть по его правилам. и я увидела человека, который просто боится. я больше не видела сильного и страшного агрессора. я видела перед собой жертву. 
когда агрессор приходит на психотерапию - он работает не со своей агрессией. он работает с насилием, которое он пережил. агрессия - это его способ защитить свои границы, которые нарушали очень грубо и долго. она становится не нужна, когда человек умеет выстраивать границы, и прорабатывает тот травматичный опыт, который привел его к позиции агрессора. 
нет, я не защищаю агрессоров. я считаю, что всем нужно работать над собой, независимо роли. 
потому что насилие порождает насилие. всегда.
#психологкакстильжизни
#16днейпротивнасилия

за силу . когда-то я даже спорила с преподом о том , что мужчина , который плачет на глазах у женщины - он демонстрирует силу , или слабость？ я считаю , что силу （если не делает это через день , конечно 😊） . потому что показать свои слабые места - это смело . сказать : “ мне здесь больно . сюда не лезь , пожалуйста ” - это сильно , потому что человек будет знать , что вам здесь больно , и сможет использовать это как для вас , так и против вас . это требует от человека в первую очередь признать в себе свои больные места , и не нападать на окружающих по поводу и без . а это ой какая работа над собой . агрессоры часто могут казаться сильными , но это не так . вы видели когда-то , чтобы они искренне говорили о своих чувствах , не манипулируя？ вы видидели , чтобы они говорили о том , что для них тяжело , при этом не требуя ничего？ это звучит парадоксально , но жертва с агрессором - одинаково слабы . потому что любой агрессор - всегда в прошлом жертва . просто агрессор в какой-то момент решил не быть , а казаться сильным и могучим . но это не так . наверное , я это пишу , чтобы самой окончательно выйти из этой роли . однажды , я , находясь в абьюзивных отношениях （токсичных , другими словами） - сказала “ мы расстаемся ” , и просто перестала играть по его правилам . и я увидела человека , который просто боится . я больше не видела сильного и страшного агрессора . я видела перед собой жертву . когда агрессор приходит на психотерапию - он работает не со своей агрессией . он работает с насилием , которое он пережил . агрессия - это его способ защитить свои границы , которые нарушали очень грубо и долго . она становится не нужна , когда человек умеет выстраивать границы , и прорабатывает тот травматичный опыт , который привел его к позиции агрессора . нет , я не защищаю агрессоров . я считаю , что всем нужно работать над собой , независимо роли . потому что насилие порождает насилие . всегда . сихологкакстильжизни

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
sometimes women learn the hard way of what it means to freeze in the face of danger. it's a learned habit, sometimes even when no danger is present. body language can speak a thousand words. there is a difference between consent and vacancy. never assume her silence is consent.
— b o d y  l a n g u a g e
© sarah doughty
.
think about this. if she's making eyes, it doesn't mean consent. if she's barely dressed, it doesn't mean consent. did it ever occur to you that asking if it's okay is not only sexy, but empowering? if she doesn't say yes, the answer is no.
.
.
you might be wondering why i'm sharing this now. you may wonder why anyone with a story of abuse or assault may wait decades before coming forward — if they ever say anything at all. the answer is simple: any time is a good time. the issue is unfortunate. that there's not enough people talking about this and how important it is to not only know the difference, but to stop blaming the victims. start conversations. teach your children what's okay and what is not. just do something.
.
and right now, that's exactly what i'm doing. 'we will not be silenced' is an important anthology of poetry, prose, essays, and even art for everyone — survivors, victims, help centers, and even law enforcement. and yes, you. find more information about this book and what you can do to help on my website.
.
#metoo
.
if you want to learn more about my free books and where to get them, head to the link in my bio and click on book links.
.

.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
the time i admired my baby momma...
.
.
i use to dislike my baby momma...like low key despise her.  i’d criticize her parenting skills, questioned the types of people she kept around my daughter, or often wondered if she was a good parent at all...to be 💯. years removed, couple custody battles later i’ve had the honor and privilege of sharing custody of my daughter 50/50 for some time now.
.
.
it’s interesting cuz i now realize and have to admit that i’ve been working from a male privilege.  truth is i don’t know what it’s like to be her and have her experience.  i don’t know what it’s like to be a woman in this patriarchal society.  i don’t know what it’s like to be a mom in a world that calls you selfish when you wanna further your career or go after your dreams.  i don’t know what it’s like to be an african-american woman in a country that says they value you but constantly shows you otherwise. .
.
me and her mom didn’t work out but i appreciate, value, and admire everything her mom has gone through and continues to go through.  my little girl’s life is going to be hard (a woman’s life is) so i’m just thankful she has an example of what a strong woman looks like.  and i’m a lot of things...i’m a dad, i’m an ally to the movement, i’m a songwriter, but one thing i’m not is critical and petty to the most important woman in my little girl’s life...not anymore.  and to the baby mommas out there...i 👀 you and i 🙌🏾 you 💜💜
.
.
✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨

.

text:
do you feel like you don’t know enough about rape culture? are you curious about how rape culture affects a person’s life and their community?
i have read this book two times within the last three years; once during my junior year and again this year. every read leaves me inspired to take action. missoula: rape and the justice system in a college town is accounts multiple student rapes at university of montana in missoula. this book is a good book to introduce people into the topic of rape culture. at the very beginning of the book, krakauer states that he chose the town of missoula to do his research because it was once dubbed the “rape capital” of the united states but he emphasized the fact that rape is happening at almost every college. i like that krakauer states that rape is more common on college campuses than people think but also that he shows you a deeper look into what campus assault truly is like and how everyone (the victim, the accused, the police, the family, the community, etc.) reacts and is affected by it. make sure to check out this book!
#sexualassault #rape #metoo #campusrape #collegerape #stopcampusassault #endcampusassault #bookstagram #jonkrakauer #missoula
name: End Campus Assault
tweet_full:
do you feel like you don’t know enough about rape culture? are you curious about how rape culture affects a person’s life and their community?
i have read this book two times within the last three years; once during my junior year and again this year. every read leaves me inspired to take action. missoula: rape and the justice system in a college town is accounts multiple student rapes at university of montana in missoula. this book is a good book to introduce people into the topic of rape culture. at the very beginning of the book, krakauer states that he chose the town of missoula to do his research because it was once dubbed the “rape capital” of the united states but he emphasized the fact that rape is happening at almost every college. i like that krakauer states that rape is more common on college campuses than people think but also that he shows you a deeper look into what campus assault truly is like and how everyone (the victim, the accused, the police, the family, the community, etc.) reacts and is affected by it. make sure to check out this book!
#sexualassault #rape #metoo #campusrape #collegerape #stopcampusassault #endcampusassault #bookstagram #jonkrakauer #missoula

text:
lydia o’connor and tyler kingkade of huffington post wrote an article that talks about rape being a national problem. i think a big problem in our society is that we don’t always see how serious a problem is, especially rape on college campuses and this is exactly what o’connor and kingkade point out in their article. 
the great thing about this article is that it identifies all the information that most people don’t know about when it comes to rape culture and presents and explains them. o’connor and kingkade even address how we define rape. different states have different definitions of sexual assault. while some states consider rape to be penetration of a penis or foreign object into a vagina or rectum, california defines it to only be the penetration of a penis into a vagina or rectum.
another great thing about this article is that it recognizes that just because a victim does not immediately pursue legal action, this does not mean that they are lying or that we should discount them. victims do not always go to police right away due to multiple reasons, whether it is embarrassment or fear, but when they finally tell they’re story, you shouldn’t discredit them.
https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/sexual-assault-explainer_us_5759aa2fe4b0ced23ca74f12
#sexualassault #rape #metoo #campusrape #collegerape #stopcampusassault #endcampusassault

text:
in june of 2011, npr released an interview where host neal conan talked to multiple people about rape. while this interview is great in that it provides opinions from a variety of people (an emt, a victim, an executive director of end violence against women international, etc.), the information seems to be more opinion based rather than fact based. 
one thing that i liked about this interview was when a caller had brought up the point about whether victims should be called victims or alleged victims. conan had stated that while we often do call them victims, the correct term is alleged victim under the presumption of innocence. on the other hand, archambault, the executive director of end violence against women international, states that in law enforcement, you wouldn’t say alleged robbery. a victim is someone who is making a statement, no different than a witness or a perpetrator.
what do you think? should we call them victims or alleged victims?
https://www.npr.org/2011/06/14/137176788/many-rape-victims-say-justice-system-still-fails-them
#sexualassault #rape #metoo #campusrape #collegerape #stopcampusassault #endcampusassault #departmentofjustice #doj

text:
r e a l  t a l k // parent’s night
#advocate #idaho ——————————————————————
on december 6, the family crisis center will host a “real talk—parent’s night” discussion focused on the effects of teen sexting in southeastern idaho.

the session will focus on the reality of sexting, the severity of the emotional and legal consequences associated with it, and parenting tips for handling these delicate situations.

we know parents want to help their children navigate these sorts of situations, but they don't always know how to do so. our goal with this parent's night is to equip parents with the knowledge and skills they need to appropriately and effectively help their teens with this issue.

the session will be held in the madison library community room at 6:30 p.m.

text: my heart. in honor of @joebiden being here in phx this evening for the second night of the arizona speaker series, i wanted to share a little something that m wrote. when i proposed the idea of writing him a letter, she was a bit cautious. “what do i thank him for? there’s so much!” so, while i was in a phx costco, we spoke on the phone about the many things that my best friend joe has helped with (or spearheaded!) m knows a bit about vawa and the it’s on us campaign as we’ve discussed the impact both have had in the work i did with survivors of sexual violence. she knows that because of vawa, survivors don’t have to pay for their code-r exams or medications needed to keep them healthy in the aftermath of their assault. that’s a huge deal, as money is almost always a huge barrier to folks accessing medical help. she knows that the biden foundation recently launched a campaign that supports the lgbtqia+ communities, raising awareness about youth suicides and lack of access to safe healthcare. (this is a cause that is extremely dear to m’s heart, as equality is basically her favorite concept ever.) i’m so proud to share information like this with my child. she may not have come from my body, but i see regular evidence that she is from my heart. a constant defender and supporter of folks who are unable to advocate for themselves, she’s an incredible friend and classmate. and that writing? the way she phrased that closing sentence?! my word. do i sense a potential flair for public (political?!) speaking in her future?! her story is really just beginning. i’m so glad she’s got joe, dr. biden, and the rest of the @bidenfoundation team to lay a bit of the way for her. she won’t ever stop fighting. neither will i, sweet pea. i won’t stop fighting either. #raisingafeminist #vp44 #vicepresidentbiden #azss #arizonaspeakerseries #kpluszplusm #itsonus #startbybelieving #kjpwritesnovels #equality #translivesmatter #metoo

text:
god sent her into my life to save me from the darkness i allowed to consume me...
.
i might delete this part later but lemme be transparent for a moment...
.
this time last year i had severe depression, suicidal thoughts, and self harm addiction. i struggled with flash backs and nightmares that are ptsd related. i sought out biblical counseling because i knew if i stayed quiet any longer about my struggles, i wouldn't make it to the end of the week.
not long after i stopped counseling, i had a relapse and that's when my older sister told us she was pregnant. the first time i held this little girl in my arms, i cried silently as she slept. i thought, "she is the reason isn't she, god? she's the reason you told me to stay alive."
many, many times i have relapsed and god's grace has been more than enough to keep me going but sometimes finding "small" things like this baby helps give me the extra push to get to the next day.
depression is not a incurable disease. it's a fleeting emotion that you have to work through just like with anger and worry. we all struggle with things like anxiety and depression differently and to different extents. no one is ever alone in life. it's impossible to be alone. even if all 7 billion humans on earth cannot fathom caring for you one bit, you have a creator who loved you at least enough to give you the breath you just took.
if anyone is ever feeling depressed or if you just want to talk, man, just dm me and we'll have a blast. i've had some pretty dark hours and i've seen the recesses of the mind and all it's terror... but i've also had the most joyful days that are filled to the brim with thankfulness. i was never always happy on either of those types of days but neither was i always sad.
please reach out to anyone, if not me. just don't hesitate.
.
that was a long moment to be transparent...
.
some tags to reach some people in need maybe??
#depression #anxiety #ptsd #assault #selfharm #awareness #gethelp #dmmeguys #reachout #notalone #stayalive #breath #itsokay #itsokaynottobeokay #struggle #metoo #christ #helovesyou #hediedforyou #dontwait

text:
veteran's suicide rates have remained between 22 and 45 veteran's a day for many years now.

its clearer than ever that the veteran's administration can not fight this alone.

there are many non profits that have stepped up to confront this war of returning home from combat unprepared to handle the effects of combat mental and physical injuries. 
we stand ready to engage this epademic head on. with your generous donation of any amount we together can save lives. 
we are to date one of a kind program that offers military veteran's and first responders a chance to learn an instrament and graduate with the gear they need to follow up with our recovery group's. 
we can not do this without you.

please answer the call of our nations heroes as they return home from answering the call to action of finding and destroying terroristic threats both foriegn and domestic.

we also accept new and gently used gear.

our programs includes instrament, post production, audio engineering, live sound, theater, film, photography, and media lessons all given free through our volunteer community of well qualified instructors. 
100% of your donations go to providing our graduates with the gear they need to continue there new hobbies with our groups of graduate veteran's. 
we can never thank you enough.

please donate to our go fund me.

https://www.gofundme.com/4j0nfyg

we look forward to the release of 
our web page soon as it is under 
construction.

all donations are only for our non profit 
pay it forward production's inc. 501c3 .

text:
we had some time at the end of our shoot so i asked if we could get a couple nursing photos so we could have a special memory of this tiny chapter in our lives.

as i’ve shared before, nursing was very scary for me. being a survivor of sexual trauma, i wasn’t comfortable with my body being on demand for someone else. i knew i would essentially lose the ability to have privacy and the ability to say “no,” because now i was nurturing someone else. someone else that needed me. i still have some challenges with this that arise when nursing margo becomes harder - like when she’s crawling on me, kicking, twiddling, pinching, etc.

margo came out of the womb and was ready to latch. like, suckling the second she was handed to me. we had some minor issues in the beginning with shitty lactation consultants trying to push nipple covers on us - but again, we’ve overcome our challenges and mostly, nursing is a walk in the park, especially considering some of the stories i’ve heard.

of course, as i mentioned, my past with sexual trauma can be a hurdle, but we overcome them, we work on them. together. without her even knowing.
and it’s because of my daughter than i am a better person. it’s because of my daughter that i have been able to heal old wounds or even begin to address them to begin with.

that’s what breastfeeding represents to me and for us. the ability to overcome challenges, whether they be physical or mental, together and by building a bond.

i think that’s a lesson we can all take away.

text:
from @gshrudayana -  hai pelaku maupun si penutup mata, kami datang lagi

siapapun, kamu diundang untuk hadir dan bergerak :)
.
hingga 10 desember kami akan bersuara lebih kencang melalui berbagai medium seni dan pertukaran narasi.

opening night enam belas film festival bali 2018 di kebun uma seminyak, jalan kayu cendana 1, oberoi, seminyak @umaseminyak registrasi dibuka 17.00 wita.

pembukaan festival tahun ini ditandai dengan screening posesif karya edwin, film pemenang penghargaan yang dengan berani menyuarakan fenomena gunung es kekerasan dalam relasi personal; pacaran. diikuti dengan #hearmetoo session bersama psikiater @dokteraidotcom yang juga salah satu pendiri @rumahberdaya_kpsibali, pengacara publik @lbh_bali, @candramertha, seorang penyintas kdp yang akan dimoderatori oleh @frischa_aswarini. diikuti oleh penampilan dari @liberal.literasi

pada opening night akan dibuka box donasi untuk ibu nuril korban pelecehan seksual yang dikriminalisasi lewat uu ite. keseluruhan rangkaian festival ini gratis, dengan himbauan membawa tumbler dan cutlery (reusable straw dsb-nya) sendiri. sebisa mungkin kita ciptakan gerakan dan dampak, bukan sampah.

sampai jumpa di #enambelasffestbali!

text:
meet julie stackhouse, our fierce & firery co-producer & first assistant director. philadelphia native, julie stackhouse is a sag-aftra actor and producer who has been acting on film and stage since the age of ten. she studies her craft at playhouse west philadelphia under the instruction of tony savant. producing for julie began four years ago and she attributes her success to the many years she spent working in the corporate world focusing on training sales & marketing teams. although her passion lies in front of the lens, she's co-founded production company, bufad cinema, in order to continue working in the industry regularly.  she is best known for it's not my fault (2018), to avenge (2018), and they are strangers (2017). www.juliestackhouse.com

text:
tarana burke @taranajaneen #metoo was the first of 31 speakers over 3 days and 6 sessions. we sprang to our feet and tears came to my eyes. this is a warrior. she is one of those people who steps out of her comfort zone to make a difference. 
this was not a business conference for me. this was a people conference. i met people from everywhere in the world, who do things i don’t do (no other hair professionals here) and listened to people who are making change happen. being here was an incredible gift. thank you to my team for doing what they do, taking amazing care of our guests—so i could be here to receive this inspiration, information, and education.  i’m inspired—beyond words. the speakers were amazing. @tedwomen2018 #tedwomen2018 #makingadifference #beinspired

text:
“i have said no too a lot of things in my life. for one, i said no to stop seeing my father. ever since i was about 7 my mom and dad went to court and fought for visitation. i was always in the middle- having to talk to law guardians and going back and forth and asking “was this my fault” or “why can’t we just be one big happy family?” but at the end i lived with my mom and visited my dad. as the years went on my dad was horrible to me. he never did anything fun with me, made me wear clothes that were too small and that were for boys. he wanted me to be his son that he didn’t have. fed me shit about my mom, said horrible things to her, i felt so uncomfortable and sad and not myself around him and his wife until one day i finally said no too visiting him, then next i knew visitations and calls ended. haven’t seen him in 3 and a half years and haven’t talked in 2 1/2. the next thing i said no to was my uncle. he got so mad at my mom and i ans hit us,i was 14 at the time. and he hit me ans i cried the whole day. i asked myself “did i deserve this” ans “why would this happen” but then i said no that this would not happen again, i wouldn’t let it happen, and if it ever did all contact would be cut. (my life is complicated with my uncle). my next no story would be me hurting myself and suicidal thoughts. i have mental illnesses and i thought life would be better if i wasn’t here, i hurt myself a lot but had stop but i still work everyday to stop it from ever happening again. i say no to this because i will not let my mental illnesses control me and my life and i won’t let my scars define me, they are apart of me and make me who i am, it’s all a battle i fought but it doesn’t define me. my last no story is, not taking shit from anybody for me being lesbian, who i am and who i love. i will not take shit from friends or family because it is who i am, it is me and love is love and there shouldn’t be no “standards” to love or stereotypes.” - @sararose03
#november #saraarmy #rosearmy #fatpositive #metoo #lovewins #together #womenempowerment

text:
i finally feel good enough to go back to painting. i picked up a respiration mask to block the fumes from getting into my lungs while i’m healing . if you read the medium piece i posted a couple of weeks back, you know i had sketched out a painting that i had hoped it would be cathartic to complete. stuck in bed these weeks, i’ve painted it in my mind 1000 times. today i actually painted it and indeed it was healing. having transformed the sexual predator into art his energy is neutralized. and so it goes with transcendence. 
here’s the piece if you missed it: 
https://link.medium.com/obrztvwghs.  #metoo

text:
betty jean owens, was abducted and brutally raped by four white men in tallahassee, florida in 1959. ms. owens’ bold testimony in front of an all-white, all-male jury in a segregated courtroom was a major catalyst for the civil rights movement and the women’s rights movement.

she testified about sexual assault before anyone held speak outs, took back the night, or said #metoo. her courage to speak out, in spite of the odds stacked against black women and girls like her. her grandson, @amontemartin is coordinating a letter-writing campaign for his grandmother. basically we write letters to betty jean owens about how her refusal to be silenced and dismissed in 1959 inspires us; how her testimony made it possible for others to speak out; and/or how her resistance to (racialized) sexual violence remains an inspiration to survivors everywhere, especially women of color who are [still] too often silenced, ignored or dismissed. to read more about betty jean owens and how you can send a letter to betty, please read the article or links...

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
- she [rebekah mercer] loved me. she was like, oh we need more of your type on our side!

your type? - the gays. she loved the gays. so did steve [bannon]. he saw us as early adopters. he figured, if you can get the gays on board, everyone else will follow. it’s why he was so into the whole milo [yiannopoulos] thing.

robert mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading – which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs – and he listened to wylie’s pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridge’s psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans. - in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas it’s the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
oi? 🙄

reportagem: a revista norte-americana time incluiu o presidente eleito jair bolsonaro em uma enquete que vai ajudar a decidir quem é a personalidade do ano, que estampa a tradicional capa da edição de dezembro da publicação.
na votação, que ocorre no site da revista, o brasileiro disputa com outros 54 nomes dos mais variados campos, entre eles os presidentes donald trump (eua) e xi jinping (china), o príncipe herdeiro da arábia saudita, mohammed bin salman, o fundador e ceo da amazon, jeff bezos, o cantor kanye west, a duquesa meghan markle, esposa do príncipe harry, e os mergulhadores tailandeses que resgataram um grupo de meninos em uma caverna da tailândia, em julho.
apesar de abrir votação, a time adverte que a escolha final recai sobre os editores da revista e que a enquete “provê informações relevantes sobre a opinião pública, dando aos leitores uma chance de influenciar na escolha”. em 2017, a publicação escolheu o movimento #metoo, que denunciou nas redes sociais casos de assédio e abuso sexual, como pessoa do ano.
no momento, a votação é liderada pelo grupo pop sul-coreano bts. bolsonaro está em antepenúltimo lugar na lista.

text: okay! i think it's time to get a little bit beyond skin deep here *** will be vulnerable so if that's not your thing, well, bye ✌ *** so i am beyond excited to announce that i have decided to become a coach!💥 a health and wellness coach with beachbody. i have a ways to go on my goal but i am so excited to share my journey and hopefully help some people along the way!!🤞 to really dig deep, it all started 4.5 years ago... i was in a toxic, abusive relationship. pregnant for the first time, in a small city living 3 hours from my family. things were scary sometimes, and it really changes the way you think day to day when you've lived in such a way. so i started looking into personal development, getting more into health and fitness but i never really took action!💥 to be perfectly honest i didn't even fully take action until 2.5 months after having my second baby! 👶💁‍♀️ but once i was cleared to start exercising again i just knew i to fully commit to this change. once i learned i could take my journey and try to make a difference i figured why the hell not!? •• i still have my bad days, everyone does we are only human! let's love each other • let's support each other • let's be there for each other! i am only hoping to give others the inspiration that got me to where i am today! #anybody can do #anything they set their #mind to! 💪💥✌•• picture from april 16th 2016 celebrating my daughters 2nd birthday 💕🎉🎁

text:
la centro nacional de explotación sexual de estados unidos ha condenado baby, la nueva serie italiana de netflix, por “normalizar el abuso sexual infantil y el tráfico sexual de menores como prostitución”. empecemos por el principio, baby se centra “un grupo de adolescentes romanas que desafían a la sociedad en su búsqueda de identidad e independencia”, entiendo “desafiar la sociedad” como vender su cuerpo siendo menores de edad para poder así conseguir un dinero extra, argumento que ha sido repudiado por el centro nacional de explotación sexual de estados unidos, el cual ha emitido un comunicado que expresa lo siguiente:

a pesar de estar en la zona cero del movimiento #metoo, netflix se ha quedado sordo con respecto a las realidades de la explotación sexual. a pesar de las quejas de los sobrevivientes del tráfico sexual, los expertos en la materia y los proveedores de servicios sociales, netflix promueve el tráfico sexual insistiendo en transmitir baby. claramente, netflix está priorizando las ganancias sobre las víctimas de abuso. no hay absolutamente nada de vanguardista acerca de la explotación sexual de menores. esta serie glamoriza el abuso sexual y trivializa la experiencia de incontables mujeres y hombres menores de edad que han sufrido el tráfico sexual.

la serie está basada en la historia real de dos chicas, 14 y 15 años, que vivían en una de las zonas más lujosas de roma en 2014, quienes se dedicaban a la prostitución en una red a la que eran frecuentes varias personalidades importante de italia, hecho que sacudió al país .

por ahora, netflix ha ignorado estas críticas y baby está disponible en la plataforma desde hoy.
name: Cochino Pop
tweet_full:
la centro nacional de explotación sexual de estados unidos ha condenado baby, la nueva serie italiana de netflix, por “normalizar el abuso sexual infantil y el tráfico sexual de menores como prostitución”. empecemos por el principio, baby se centra “un grupo de adolescentes romanas que desafían a la sociedad en su búsqueda de identidad e independencia”, entiendo “desafiar la sociedad” como vender su cuerpo siendo menores de edad para poder así conseguir un dinero extra, argumento que ha sido repudiado por el centro nacional de explotación sexual de estados unidos, el cual ha emitido un comunicado que expresa lo siguiente:

a pesar de estar en la zona cero del movimiento #metoo, netflix se ha quedado sordo con respecto a las realidades de la explotación sexual. a pesar de las quejas de los sobrevivientes del tráfico sexual, los expertos en la materia y los proveedores de servicios sociales, netflix promueve el tráfico sexual insistiendo en transmitir baby. claramente, netflix está priorizando las gacias sobre las víctimas de abuso. no hay absolutamente nada de vanguardista acerca de la explotación sexual de menores. esta serie glamoriza el abuso sexual y trivializa la experiencia de incontables mujeres y hombres menores de edad que han sufrido el tráfico sexual.

la serie está basada en la historia real de dos chicas, 14 y 15 años, que vivían en una de las zonas más lujosas de roma en 2014, quienes se dedicaban a la prostitución en una red a la que eran frecuentes varias personalidades importante de italia, hecho que sacudió al país .

por ahora, netflix ha ignorado estas críticas y baby está disponible en la plataforma desde hoy.

text:
hi friends,

i have been very absent in here, so thanks to those who have stuck around and are still following support. 💞

i've been carrying a pretty bad injury in my hip flexor which has played part in my absence in the exercising realm, so there's that. 
but most of my absence has been to a toxic & hostile working environment. people on "power highs" stomping on anyone they can just go feel a little more higher. i went back into emotional eating because part of our adoption journey is that we are both meant to be employed and/or receiving maternity leave so i felt really trapped in having to stay there. my anxiety peaked & all i could manage was transforming into a new burrito with endless supplies of food. 
i quit two weeks ago after the manager trapped me in a room and harassed me to the point i had panic attack, nosebleeds and passed out.

the decision in itself relieved me of so much pressure, it was surreal. i've been spending the last few weeks mentally healing through self-care & meditation. 
december is the month where we start at a new beginning and exercise challenge to work through the physical side of things & through it. 💞💃💞

text:
"listening with compassion is not enough. action needs to be taken." - karen rain 
even if it is the smaller shift in perspective or language or speaking up in a situation where you would normally stay quiet. an internal shift is a shift, and is action. a modification of behavior is action. a commitment to being better today than you were yesterday is action.

this is inspired by the j.brown podcast interviewing karen rain, about pattabhi jois and the ashtanga community's response to her (and others') statements about jois' sexual abuse. 
#metoo is also in the yoga community.

i especially appreciate that after the podcast, was an addendum where karen called jason brown and asked him some tough and challenging questions, while asking him to see where he could make a difference. and i thank jason for publicly hearing karen, and accepting the difficult conversation. 
jason in this difficult position exemplifies what many white males need to be doing, to hear the conversation, own their role in it, and do the work to modify behavior in such a way that tomorrow will be better than today.

most importantly, this is not to say that jason did anything "wrong" and that is the tricky thing in this movement, the majority have not done anything wrong so to speak, but in subtle and unconscious ways, we all are complicit in perpetuating the situation, until we are ready to look at the really hard truth of how we are adding to it.

we can all make a difference! in fact, it is a responsibility that we do! #makeadifference #metoo #metooyoga #phoenixrisingyogatherapy #yogateacher #yogamama #yogatherapy #embodiedmindfulness #intentionalliving #livelifebetter

text:
#fbf | march 1962. a house party in palm springs, ca. norma is next to marilyn when he has a flashback of her childhood and her mother at coldwater canyon drive. it was 1934, fire season, the middle of the night. gladys, half-drunk, is driving with baby norma while the fires are spreading on the hills. 
why are we going uphill, mother… why, on this night of fire? 
your daddy’s private mansion is uphill, at the top, don’t you want to go? 
a police officer stops them at a barricade: it’s not safe, and invites them to drive back home. gladys is angry and evasive: i was invited to a private mansion on laurel canyon. the owner has a fire-proof house. my daughter and i will be safe there… this is the city of sand and nothing can last here, but we are going there.

to settle here was a mistake. the city of sand, your father used to call it... because it’s built on sand and is sand. it’s a desert! mankind isn’t meant to live in such a place! so, we’re being punished. for our pride and our stupidity.

and norma wakes up suddenly, with a scream.
_______________

text_retweet: #repost @psych_bytes what is emdr??? this is usually one of the first questions i get from women starting their trauma healing journey...#emdr is one of the most researched models for trauma therapy..in the last 20 years the federal government has funded major studies for emdr to help war veterans. this is a highly effective and powerful model for reducing symptoms of #ptsd, sometimes within a few sessions! however, only trained mental health professionals should be doing emdr, because if not done correctly it may re-traumatize a person. if you are considering emdr therapy make sure to find a provider that has trained at an emdria-approved program. #mentalhealthawareness #emdrtherapy #metoo #traumatherapy #innerhealing4women

text:
rising: sittin’ on your soul (2/14) by nicholas jones, 07 october 2017. -

you’re the kind of beautiful that‘s sittin’ on the soul,
the kind that gives truth to everything i’ve ever known,
you’re the first and the last - the beginning of my joy and the end of my suffering,
you’re the hope and love that joy can bring,
and you’re never alone when you’re with me - sleeping beauty,

with the calm of aphrodite’s eyes and the rage of medusa’s bones,
you have a way about you that can turn a man to stone,
you’re an introspective point of view that infernos couldn’t hold candles to,
you’re the way through the darkness when i’m lost in the void,
and the way through the rubble after it’s all been destroyed,

i want to lay next to you for the rest of my days - together we’ll stand, 
i want to make you smile - and count all of the ways that i can,
i want you to be what distinguishes my life from the rest of the world,
and every day - i’ll count the minutes from the moment you leave,
until you make your way back home to me,

you’re the kind of beautiful that’s sitting on my soul,
and every time i’m with you - something else takes hold of me,
i hold you as you hold me together - the rescuer and the refugee,
two birds of one feather flock together - there’s not a single storm that we can’t weather,
when i’m standing next to you - so let’s turn on the radio,

we can light candles across the living room - and play our favorite song,
about the lovers who spend their whole lives singing along whenever it comes on,
you’re everything i ever wanted to need and to be - the truth completely,
and if the truth should be told - for the rest of my life - you’re the only one i want to hold,
for you i’ll be what you are to me - i’ll be the kind of beautiful that’s sittin’ on your soul.
name: The Poetry of Nicholas Jones

text:
a roy lichtenstein inspired #metoo campaign.
i've had an urge to make some political art after a close friend of mine told me she had recently been raped. 
first of all i am so proud and inspired by her bravery, speaking openly and honestly about her experience. i can barely speak about my own experience and yet it haunts me every day. 
i was a child the first time it happened and again as a teenager, i didn't know what sex was let alone consent. i think a lot of the confusion, frustration, shame and self hatred comes from thinking i had asked for it, like it was my fault because i didn't speak up or put up a fight. being underage is not consent, silence is not consent, just going along with it is not consent, being drunk or asleep or in a vulnerable position is not consent!
consent is an active choice and a process that requires ongoing conversations that allow you to change your mind at anytime. 
nobody asks to be raped or sexually asaulted and it is never the victims fault!
name: Evie Angeline White

text:
rising: i wont forget (3/14) by nicholas jones, 18 september 2018.

i won’t forget about you - so don’t you ever forget about me,
the way we talked in our sleep - or through the lack there-of,

i won’t forget about the ride - and swinging around from side to side,
finding meaning in the moonlight - and then moving further away from it,

i won’t forget the passing of time - or how the fire was all we idolized,
then as time continued on - became what we grew to despise,

i won’t forget the happy times - or the way you laughed and smiled,
as if the world stopped completely -  but only for a little while,

and i won’t forget your hand - finding mine in the dark,
when i cried - while the world was falling apart,

so when you’re having a bad day - just know someone remembers you,
so when you’re sitting on the lonely side - just know i’m lonely too,
so when you need someone to hug and smile - i’ll be here for a while,
and when and if you need me too - then i just hope you know that i won’t forget you,

we once dreamed about the day that we’d get out of here,
but now we live in fear that we won’t make it in time,
but baby i promise that on the seventh day,
god will rest in the clouds and i’ll be here to pick you up,
the best way that i know how - and i promise i won’t forget you.
name: The Poetry of Nicholas Jones

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
#notallmen
.
.
women hear this a lot. “not all men.” i think men feel attacked or that the finger is pointed specifically at them when women speak about #metoo and abuse by men.

and of course it doesn’t feel good to feel like you’re being criticized or attacked. 
i think your intentions are trying to say “hey! i’m not this way and i respect women, so ‘not all men.’” if you’re a man and are saying “not all men” i need you to know something...and i need you to hear me.

when i (and other women) overwhelmingly in large numbers come out to share about our horrible abuse and experiences and your response is “not all men” this is what you’re doing. you’re: • minimizing my experience • telling me my experience is invalid
•telling me my experience is unimportant •denying and defending the behavior of other men
•not being part of the solution

the thing is, i (sadly) don’t know a woman who hasn’t been assaulted or harassed. not one. 
so if every woman i know, and every woman they know, has faced sexual assault and/or harassment and/or domestic violence by the hands of a man, then us asking why “men” continue to perpetuate this culture shouldn’t be controversial. 
if you’re not part of the problem, then be a part of the solution. want to know how you can help? just ask!♥️ .
.
.

text:
(español abajo) on saturday november 3rd, @metmuseum became the site of a guerilla performance project, zoning in on the abusive behavior of the male artists that line its walls. artist @michellehartneyart’s performance/call to action subverted displays of artists such as balthus, paul gauguin and pablo picasso, by applying her own series of wall plaques across the galleries to highlight their misogyny. while hartney stressed that she is not advocating censorship of artworks, she argues that museums must do more to educate the public about the darker side of the artists that they venerate. the museum removed hartney’s texts when they were discovered by staff.
.
.
.
el sábado 3 de noviembre, @metmuseum se volvió el sitio de un proyecto de performance de guerrilla enfocado en el comportamiento abusivo de los artistas masculinos que cubren sus paredes. el llamado a la acción/performance de la artista @michellehartneyart subvirtió las exhibiciones de artistas como balthus, paul gauguin y pablo picasso al aplicar su propia serie de placas de pared en las galerías para resaltar sus misoginias. si bien hartney enfatizó no estar pugnando por la censura de las obras de arte, argumentó que los museos deben hacer más para educar al público sobre el lado más oscuro de los artistas que veneran. el museo removió los textos de hartney cuando los descubrió su personal.
.

tweet_full:
(español abajo) on saturday november 3rd, @metmuseum became the site of a guerilla performance project, zoning in on the abusive behavior of the male artists that line its walls. artist @michellehartneyart’s performance/call to action subverted displays of artists such as balthus, paul gauguin and pablo picasso, by applying her own series of wall plaques across the galleries to highlight their misogyny. while hartney stressed that she is not advocating censorship of artworks, she argues that museums must do more to educate the public about the darker side of the artists that they venerate. the museum removed hartney’s texts when they were discovered by staff.
.
.
.
el sábado 3 de noviembre, @metmuseum se volvió el sitio de un proyecto de performance de guerrilla enfocado en el comportamiento abusivo de los artistas masculinos que cubren sus paredes. el llamado a la acción/performance de la artista @michellehartneyart subvirtió las exhibiciones de artistas como balthus, paul gauguin y pablo picasso al aplicar su propia serie de placas de pared en las galerías para resaltar sus misoginias. si bien hartney enfatizó no estar pugdo por la censura de las obras de arte, argumentó que los museos deben hacer más para educar al público sobre el lado más oscuro de los artistas que veneran. el museo removió los textos de hartney cuando los descubrió su personal.
.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

.
so, at the start of @unwomen 16 days of activism my #techforgood agency @ukcultureshift are making a pledge:
1. we will listen to survivors
2. we will stand up for justice
3. we will say #heartmetoo
.
1 in 3 women experiences violence in their lifetime. join us in saying no to violence against women and girls, and say we will #believewomen.
.

hola mis lectores. hoy vengo con un tema que todos sabemos que ya se ha vuelto bastante común y eso, eso duele. me duele que estos temas se vuelvan comunes, que sea normal esto que está sucediendo, saben de qué hablo? del acoso sexual, de las violaciones. 
particularmente he sido acosada sexualmente en varias ocasiones y esto no quiere decir que me han violado o me han tocado, pero ya con el simple hecho de una mirada abusiva y palabras nada simpáticas ya es un acoso sexual. 
en un trabajo que antes tuve recibí mucho acoso por parte de mi jefe y eso me hacía sentir tan asqueada y tan nerviosa en muchas ocasiones. 
no entiendo porque no han terminado de entender que no nos gusta basta, no queremos ser el centro de atención de esa manera, ¿porque siempre quieren llamar nuestra atención con actitudes tan estúpidas? ¿tan asquerosas? basta, no queremos que nos vean como un pedazo de carne jugoso, ni queremos que nos vean como las dulces mariposas que creen que somos, solo somos seres humanos y ya trátenos como tal, como cualquier persona, que cada historia se haga saber porque así es la única manera de hacernos escuchar, porque si yo quiero salir a la calle con un short corto eso no te da derecho a ti a violarme, ni te estoy provocando, no te da derecho a acosarme y muchos menos te da derecho a asesinarme. vivimos situaciones que nos da miedo estar solas en un mismo salón con un hombre no se vuelvan eso a lo que terminamos temiendole, y lo peor de todo son las palabras de la sociedad, donde dicen cosas como “ ella no tuvo que haber salido así” “ ella no tuvo que haberlo provocado” “ seguro ella algo hizo” ahora la culpa es de nosotras? por ser violadas y asesinadas por un enfermo que su pasión y su excitación está en ver sufrir a alguien más. situaciones  similares a esta evidencia como la sociedad no los detiene y como, a su vez, ve la victima como la responsable de dichas situaciones. hoy estuve leyendo un post de una conocida @r8nita en su blog muy mala mia de una situación que le sucedió a una de sus amigas y les invito a que lo lean. 
#metoo #pezoneslibres #nomasabuso #creandoycontando

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

jennifer lopez, born in the bronx, new york, is a sensational actor, dancer and singer who began with small roles in low budget films and as an extra dancer. the 18 year old girl fled away from her home to pursue her career as her parents didn't approve of her decision. 
lopez went on to received a golden globe nomination and became the first latina actress to earn over us$1 million for a film, later establishing herself as the highest-paid latin actress in hollywood.
lopez became the first woman to have a number one album and film in the same week. her 2002 remix album, j to tha l–o! the remixes, became the first in history to debut at number one on the u.s. billboard 200. 
with a cumulative film gross of us$2.9 billion and estimated global sales of 80 million records, lopez is regarded as the most influential latin performer in the united states. in 2012, forbes ranked her as the most powerful celebrity in the world, as well as the 38th most powerful woman in the world. time listed her among the 100 most influential people in the world in 2018. .

text:
barefoot & pregnant ✝️♥️🌻
every time it rains i end up barefoot, naked and pregnant... sayyyy whattttt ? 
let me tell you what i mean . here in #oc we don’t get a lot of rain and so when it pours , it invites a disruption in our day to day system. some freak out and others like me get freaky with it . i love #rain; the puddles , the sounds, the thunder and the lightning (only time i’ll run inside , a girl’s gotta live ). here is what i do when it rains: 
1- i always go into the rain/storm . this often gives us a new physical sensation . it breaks us out of the ordinary mindset .
2- i get extra with it . i sometimes run barefoot and let the dirt do it’s work . i get closer to the earth in my senses and closer to god in my heart by worshiping him 🙏 
3- i watch the crowds as they are suited and booted fighting to stay dry and tying not to get sick . i realize how many are simply programmed to do what is “right” . i on the other hand am dancing and looking foolish but not even giving one duck . ( i never get sick) 
4- i’m vulnerable and i feel naked in my soul . the first 3 steps have positioned me in a space and time that is present and in this present moment , i am one with the creator (yes i know we are always one but we don’t behave on it , hush) . ideas flood into my heart and soul and the day to day mundane, gates of routine that normally block the flow from spirit to soul to body swing open to clear the path for agape (god’s love ) .
5- new seeds are planted and i become pregnant with fresh ideas from the creator as our desires align.
i share this with you as it has been a part of me since i was a little girl. although i didn’t know god as i do now and i didn’t understand the process , i’ve been experiencing it all my life . the only difference now is that god has placed insight and wisdom within me to be more aware of what is being planted and to share it with all of you . i pray this reaches the person/people who need a fresh start . here is your message, start today , go all in and let god do his part over time. just show up and dance in the rain my friends ✝️♥️🌻
.
#wildflower #godsgrace #rainshine #plantingseeds #newday #beautiful #life

text:
from 2001 to 2003, bill clinton flew on epstein’s private plane, dubbed “the lolita express,” 26 times. epstein is close to prince andrew and was a regular at trump’s mar-a-lago.
trump told new york magazine of epstein in 2002, “terrific guy. he’s a lot of fun to be with. it is even said that he likes beautiful women as much as i do, and many of them are on the younger side.”
epstein, 65, pleaded guilty in 2008 to soliciting prostitution from a teen and served 13 months in jail.
last year, he reportedly paid millions to settle three lawsuits filed against him by teens. bannon’s rep didn’t comment. a lawyer for epstein said, “let me ask him,” but didn’t respond by deadline.

text:
when a homicide occurs in a community it causes many reactions – fear, helplessness, unrealistic expectations of the survivors, anger, rumors and assumptions about the death, investigations, and prosecution of criminal charges.  generally, the family and witnesses are asked not to discuss the case while the investigation or criminal charges are pending.
.. as a community member, you can support the survivor by not asking them pressing questions about the case or trying to gain information. the survivor is still processing the violent loss of their family member. it can be very hurtfult to feel like everyone constantly wants information from you when all you want to do is miss your loved one that is gone and mourn them. .. do not share any rumors or sensational news coverage of their loved one. let the survivor decide what information they learn about the public coverage of their loved one's death when they want to explore that, if they want to explore that. the survivor already has a lot to process. if you have pertinent information to the case, then call law enforcement yourself, rather then placing that on the shoulders of the person who is grieving. ... *november 20th until december 20th is survivors of homicide awareness month. we will be highlighting survivors of homicide periodically throughout the month as a part of access' homicide and violent crimes program*

nov 25th marked the beginning of the international "16 days of activism against gender-based violence" campaign. many celebrities all over nigeria have pledged their support in a trending video and are using their voice and social media platforms to raise awareness about this very important cause.
.
celebrities who pledged their support included #waje, #funkeakindele, #katehenshaw, #rahamasadau, #kidcomedianemmauella, #adesuaetomiwellington, #toolz, #dakoreegbuson, #omonioboli, #phyno, #cohbamsasuquo, #bankyw, #rmd, #timidakolo, #mi, #ikosakioduwa, #sanidanja, #ebuka and #utinwachukwu
.
the awareness campaign is put together by european union in nigeria, one of the 136 eu delegations around the world which officially represents the eus interests in nigeria and ecowas
.
the #16daysofactivism against gender-based violence is an international campaign to challenge violence against women and girls around the world. .
visit their website www.herstoryourstory.ng sign your pledge to join the campaign, share your badge and encourage your friends and family to lend their support.
.
if you are a victim and also seeking help you can visit the website to find a help centre near you

text: did you know that there are 460,000 sexual assaults every year in canada, but only 5% of survivors report to police.  some of the reasons for this devastatingly low percentage haven’t changed in generations.  the impact of this crime can span a lifetime when kept silenced and unhealed.  the only people that silence benefits are the perpetrators.  time to raise the bar on a stronger, educated and more fair #justicesystem. i am 1 of the 5% that reached out to both the restorative justice system and our canadian justice system.  i am here to answer any questions you might have and/or to support your journey.  please reach out, you’re not alone. #justicereform  #c337 #thejustact #metoo #courage #vulnerabilityisstrength #endstigma #csa #sa9

text:
🗣🗣 psa 🗣🗣 as you head into your weekend let me give you some food for thought. 
often times addiction is labeled. those struggling get overlooked. their voices aren’t heard. rather than turn a blind eye take a minute to listen 👂🏼. i mean really listen to them. we are all just a bunch of broken and traumatized people. 
when you can connect with someone on a mental level and encourage them to speak up, you’ve just given them the tools they need to #shatterthesilence and find true peace. and there is no drug (legal or illegal) that can give you that. it’s not a war on drugs, it’s a war on emotionally broken, traumatized, abused, and lost people. sharing your story may be exactly what someone else needed to hear to say “me too” and break the chains. 
i hear the chains falling. we are starting a movement.

#shatterthesilence #metoo #mentalhealthawareness #addictiontreatment #addiction #recovery #breakingchains #abusesurvivor #childabuseadvocate #selfloveadvocate

text:
a few tips and tricks to get you through today, tomorrow, the holiday season, and any time you find yourself caught up in your own head. you don't have to be diagnosed with an anxiety disorder to feel anxious; it is an extremely common emotion and often hard to recognize if you don't know what to look for. comment with your favorite grounding technique or something that you recognize in your mind/body as the first sign that you are getting anxious. we'd love to know! 💞
•
here is a simple one that i use when i'm freaking about workload, biting my nails and struggling to focus.
•
wherever you are, pause and then while taking deep breaths try to count the following as they apply to you and your immediate surroundings/bodily sensations...
5 things you see 👀
4 things you hear 👂
3 things you feel (i.e. the heaviness of your body in your chair, a tingling in your foot, a shaking/tightness in your chest, a smile fighting it's way to the surface) 👐
2 things you smell 👃
1 thing you taste 👅
•
•
•

text:
små tjejer - linnea henriksson 
känner en kvinna som är chef på värsta storbolaget
hon skördar lik med sina klackar, hon är riktigt farlig
hon var blyg när vi va små, så lite märkligt är det
alla säger att hon särat benen
en annan brud i samma klass, hon blev fan ingenting
hon bor kvar i samma stad, skaffat hus, familj
du vet hon jobbar inom vården, klagar ”det e' för mycket”
ingen är förvånad, och vi alla tycker ”typiskt”
hon låter ganska lat, visst?
jag låter knappast feministisk
jag ba' driver, kan inte trampa folk på tårna
måste va försiktig
lilla gumman, ta det lugnt
va inte så jävla viktig
jag vet min klocka säger tick-tick
men kanske inte vill ha barn på riktigt
kan jag säga detta riskfritt?
håll dig till din business

småtjejer blir alltid stämplade för nåt
stämpla tillbaks, normalt händelseförlopp
jag är kvalitetsstämpel utav svensk pop
men om en kvinna vågar drömma tar det jämt stopp
en queen där på toppen
dom andra slåss på botten
du får ingen ny chans om du redan fått en
man måste vässa sina klor
för alla följer trender
jag med, #metoo
”vi ser inte kön, vi ser kompetens”
dom orden låter som vi alla vore överens
men kvinnan jobbar kvar när alla män går hem
ingen lön mellan fyra-fem
det ska bli bättre för min lillasyster
men våran storebror, hans polare, dom är inte feminister
dom har råd och verkar vinna på att skita i
så länge en kvinna är bunden
är ingen av oss fri 
#words
#queen

text: “they told me i needed to have sex with the man in order to get paid." like many girls in ecuador, alicia left her rural village as a child to work as a live-in maid in neighboring colombia. promised a room of her own and good pay, she didn't know the sexual trauma she'd be forced to endure just to earn a living. alicia, now an activist and care program participant, works to protect women from sexual harassment and assault at work. sexual harassment at work affects women all around the world. you can help change that. learn more and sign the petition at the link in bio.  #thisisnotworking #16days #metoo #hearmetoo

two women, a mother and her daughter, pray at the grave of a family member who was murdered by her boyfriend. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for “femicide,” the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio.

text:
✊ #100jahrefrauenwahlrecht 💪

heute, vor genau 100 jahren, am 30.november 1918, wurde das frauenwahlrecht gesetzlich verankert.

ein großer und bedeutender tag, an dem wir dieser hart erkämpften errungenschaft und allen daran beteiligten frauen gedenken sollten! 
doch ebenso sollten wir uns deutlich vor augen halten:
ein ganzes jahrhundert später ist das #ziel der gleichen teilhabe für frauen bei weitem nicht erreicht.

noch immer kämpfen überall auf der welt #frauen, wie die friedensnobelpreisträgerin nadia murad, für ihre rechte und gegen unterdrückung!

auch der hashtag #metoo hat frauen dazu ermutigt, ihre stimme zu erheben, gegen die patriachalen machtstrukturen unserer gesellschaft.

es zeigt sich: der kampf für die gleichheit der geschlechter geht jeden tag weiter und das erreichte kann auch wieder verloren gehen. 
es ist an uns den rückfall in längst überholte rollenbilder, den rechte kräfte überall auf der welt vorantreiben, zu verhindern und weiter für echte #gleichstellung zu kämpfen! _______________________
#amiramohamedali #politik #frauenwahlrecht #wahlrecht #mdb #dielinke #follow #linksfraktion #abgeordnete #starkefrauen
name: Amira Mohamed Ali, MdB
