text:
我獨自在台(小琉球)成功報案(關於性騷擾罪) (超文)
以下是我獨自在台灣成功報案的個案，很想讓其他單身女遊客甚至全部女性都知道遇到以下的事不要害怕，就算沒有人幫，只要勇敢爭取屬於自己的權利就可以。

在19/11/2018，當我到小琉球的電動機車店租車的時候，店老闆就藉著教我騎電動自行車及腳踏車性騷擾了我，在騎車的時候坐在我後面用雙臂圍著我，說是要教我，後來在我下車的時候又拍打我屁股，又裝熱情的留我在店裡，說要請我喝東西，但我還是拒絕了。他一開始就問我住在哪，又交換了line來聯絡，說有事可以找他，所以之後他更在line裡面威脅我說知道我的住址。

其實我只是個遊客，不想告他是覺得會浪費時間，才沒有報警，但他居然在5點多傳簡訊給我，問我在幹什麼，我一怒就罵了他，最後他老羞成怒去報警，還說因為我罵他，他要告我防礙名譽。當晚警察來了，跟我了解事情，民宿老闆也跟他說之前有其他外國的單身女遊客都給他性騷擾，但大家都是來玩幾天，所以忍了就算。事實上，我跟島上其他人提起這件事，大家都知道是誰，還說得出店的名字，我不想有下一個女生中招，而且之前在印尼和馬來西亞也受過好多類似的性騷擾，卻因為害怕就沒有報警或當場罵他，這次我覺得不能再那麼懦弱，所以隔天就報警。

可是來做紀錄的警察態度很不客氣，覺得我小事化大，其實不光是他，島上的人甚至台灣女遊客都叫我不用報警，說我沒證據，大家都退縮了，好像是我的問題。昨天，我第一次感到非常失望和孤單，因為連一直知道事情的人都不會站出來，還要我這個外國人來代替他們站出來說話，每個人都好像事不關己的那樣，看到我請警察來了還給臉色我看，連一直都說可以幫我的民宿的人都退縮了(。 那個警察一來就用審問的態度問我事情經過，還一直說簡訊內容沒有威脅性（那男人說知道我住在哪，對我來說已經很威脅了好嗎），還在沒有知會我的情況下載我去那間店，要我跟那男人對話，我在途中一直說不安全，我不想跟他對話，但警察都沒說話，一直載我，幸好店已經關了門，但警察還私自打電話給他，那時候我好像完全成了局外人一樣。。。最後警察約了我跟那男人今天11點到警局對話。我整個晚上都很擔心，因為那警察的態度讓我很不安，所以今天早上我打去議員處，幸好找到一個警察前局長，他一聽到是性騷擾的事就立刻前來了解，還載我去警察局跟警察們說說話，讓他們重視一下。

我說我只是遊客，只想要一個公平的道歉，還要他不要再性騷擾其他女生了。他們勸說我不要等他來，說他反告我就不好，但我不斷的想，如果我就這樣走，事情就沒有解決，那我報警就白費了，所以我拖延時間，等到他來了，他還跟前局長說起簡訊的事，說我傷害到他，要告我，不覺得自己有問題，幸好有前局長的幫忙，最後他願意跟我好好道歉。警察們這兩天都去找他，看看他有沒有找我，說他已經成為目標，因為之前有女生嘗試告他但不成功，所以這次再來就提高警覺。

事情算是完滿結束，在這次，我看到更多人性的好和壞，壞的讓我很泄氣，想想看，如果是你或你最重視的人受到這樣對待，你還會叫她啞忍嗎？自私這心態害死很多人，啞忍不會對事情有幫助，只會令你們忍得越來越多！如果人人都可以將心比心，世界或許會少一點不公平的事發生。

p.s. 圖中就是那男人的店，請大家到小琉球小心注意，就在碼頭附近。他戴眼鏡和帽子，瘦瘦的。

#還請大家廣傳讓更多受過性騷擾的女生看到
#到了三天才開始享受
多謝我男友，我妹和她朋友，還有一個朋友的全力幫忙

可是來做紀錄的警察態度很不客氣，覺得我小事化大，其實不光是他，島上的人甚至台灣女遊客都叫我不用報警，說我沒證據，大家都退縮了，好像是我的問題。昨天，我第一次感到非常失望和孤單，因為連一直知道事情的人都不會站出來，還要我這個外國人來代替他們站出來說話，每個人都好像事不關己的那樣，看到我請警察來了還給臉色我看，連一直都說可以幫我的民宿的人都退縮了(。 那個警察一來就用審問的態度問我事情經過，還一直說簡訊內容沒有威脅性（那男人說知道我住在哪，對我來說已經很威脅了好嗎），還在沒有知會我的情況下載我去那間店，要我跟那男人對話，我在途中一直說不安全，我不想跟他對話，但警察都沒說話，一直載我，幸好店已經關了門，但警察還私自打電話給他，那時候我好像完全成了局外人一樣。。。最後警察約了我跟那男人今天11點到警局對話。我整個晚上都很擔心，因為那警察的態度讓我很不安，所以今天早上我打去議員處，幸好找到一個警察前局長，他一聽到是性騷擾的事就立刻前來了解，還載我去警察局跟警察們說說話，讓他們重視一下。

事情算是完滿結束，在這次，我看到更多人性的好和壞，壞的讓我很泄氣，想想看，如果是你或你最重視的人受到這樣對待，你還會叫她啞忍嗎？自私這心態害死很多人，啞忍不會對事情有幫助，只會令你們忍得越來越多！如果人人都可以將心比心，世界或許會少一點不公平的事發生。

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
when the ones closest to you want you to fail...
_
it’s hard to believe right?
_
every time you take a step forward you have someone there ready to crush it for you.
_
your excitement.
_
your goals.
_
your dreams.
_
know that feeling?
_
it’s confusing to say the least... you start self doubting...
_
what if they are right?
_
what if i am going to fail?
_
am i wasting my time?
_
so you hold back, you lose your enthusiasm, you start hiding in the background embarrasses to go after what you want.
_
want to know the reason why they do it?
_
more often than not, it actually has nothing to do with you.
_
most people won’t take the risk to create the life they want...that’s fine not everyone has too.
_
and quite frankly not every one should!
_
but if you want too... you are going to have to get used to the fact you won’t have everyone in your corner.
_
you are going to have to do this for you!
_
it gets easier when you surround yourself with people who inspire you...
_
those who have similar goals...
_
👊🏼 maintain your focus on what you want > when you become distracted it’s easy to listen to the opinions of others
_
👊🏼 don’t compare > this is your journey, focus on the next step for you
_
👊🏼 accept that failing is a part of growing and learning > as they say ... there’s no such thing as failure only feedback
_
if i had given up because those around me didn’t believe in me, or when those closest to me had removed me from fb or hid my status’ ... or laughed at my selfies.
_
i wouldn’t be on the journey i’m on...
_
changing the lives i change.
_
who knows who you will be letting down if you don’t follow your path...
_
the one person for sure that you will be letting down is yourself.
_
don’t stop because others want you to fail...
_
fail over and over again so you can win.

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
mgtow 101: alien vs predator

what is wickedness, what is a wicked act?

wickedness is any sin, act of sin or anything that causes sin. god said all wickedness is nothing compared to the wickedness of women.

i repeat “there is nothing on this whole planet more wicked than the acts of a woman”. you guys need to really examine this verse and think about it thoroughly.

we often project male qualities onto women. women are animalistic and primal, they aren't made with honor or loyalty.

when i explain female nature, i like to use the example of alien versus predator. the women obviously are aliens and the men are predators.

in battle, they are both vicious killers but the predator was capable of logic, compassion, honor and loyalty. if you didn't have a weapon in your hands he wouldn't kill you.

in alien vs predator, when sanaa lathan killed an alien, the predator became loyal to her. when the chief predators saw she had the markings of a predator warrior they all became loyal to her as well.

alien on the other hand, are survivors. they don't have the capacity for the traits the predator has. they will kill any human they come across, and they will even kill each other. they don't have the capacity to think "wait this is a human that scared and doesn't have a gun", they just survive by any means necessary.

this is how you should view women, they are aliens not equipped with mechanisms that can override their need to survive. no woman will go homeless and live on the streets with her kids, because of her loyalty and love for her husband. she will survive and find a new husband. she will begin looking as soon as she sees the signs of trouble.

i repeat “they were not created with honor or loyalty”. nazis defeated the polish and hella polish women gave themselves sexually to the nazis, within minutes of having their kids and husband killed. they looked at their kids and husbands dead bodies and instantly gave themselves to the ones that killed them. with lions, when a new alpha comes into the picture, the mothers will kill off the cubs and start a new pride. the cubs and alpha lion are disposable, the lionesses will survive by any means necessary.

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency
